  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One was to Murnowska and one was to Niska, N-I-S-K-A.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we live in the second frontage, Niska.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, the flats in the frontage were occupied by the rich families and the flats on the side by the poor families and all depend on store.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "On the attic, there lived a few Christian people, widows, et cetera, because there was all the sort of one room flat, and nothing like, you see, we see now, very primitive.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You see, ours was a Polish-speaking family, because my older siblings, they were at high school, and so on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was an idea that, you see, while we go, while we grow up, we should know Polish so no discrimination at school, et cetera, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And say, at that time, among neighborhood what I have [INAUDIBLE] talking that they have to speak Polish to take a place in society.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And Yiddish, they will pick up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not, not much, not unless you see some grandparents or relatives from the country came.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My Yiddish was good enough, you see.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But just the same, I could communicate.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You see, the parents spoke Yiddish is wanted to keep secrets from us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we understood every word.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And at first, on account of our Polish, to a certain period, we were not allowed to play in the courtyard, you see, with the kids, until our Polish was good enough so nothing can damage it.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Of course, a little bit of Yiddish you learned, because they brought in a teacher to of prayers, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] you see, life was going on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We didn't, in Warsaw so over the period, we didn't feel what they say today the state business.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
